# MackesWorkstation per-user control plane (mackesd serve) — enabled by default.
#
# mackesd owns the Bus / mesh / CA state the shell + Workbench consume, so on a
# workstation it should run at every login. Enabling here is what makes
# %systemd_user_post actually flip the unit on (a bare macro defers to preset
# policy, which would otherwise leave it disabled).
#
# Bug 6 (2026-06-06) is resolved: `mackesd serve` no longer crash-loops its
# fabric workers on a per-user / non-enrolled box — nebula_https_listener
# (relay :443), fs_sync (retired Python mesh-gvfs), voice_config (system path),
# and ansible-pull (fleet URL) each prereq-gate and self-skip when their
# prerequisites are absent, so a fresh workstation runs the daemon clean.
enable mackesd.service
